    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for the rename feature. It touches exactly **4 files** with no new files and no test file modifications:\n\n---\n\n### `api/types.go`\nAdd `RenameRequest` struct (after `CopyRequest`, line 765) — same shape as `CopyRequest` with `source`/`destination` fields.\n\n### `api/client.go`\nAdd `Rename(ctx, *RenameRequest) error` method (after `Delete`, line 395) — POSTs to `/api/rename`, no response body, mirrors `Copy` exactly.\n\n### `server/routes.go`\nTwo additions:\n1. **Route** — `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after the copy route (line 1698)\n2. **Handler** — `RenameHandler` after `CopyHandler` (line 1483) with this logic:\n   - JSON bind → 400 on bad body\n   - `model.ParseName` + validity check → 400 on bad names\n   - `getExistingName` normalization for both src and dst\n   - `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if source missing\n   - `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → **409** if destination already exists\n   - `CopyModel(src, dst)` → copies manifest\n   - `srcManifest.Remove()` + `srcManifest.RemoveLayers()` → deletes source manifest and orphaned blobs (layers shared with the new destination are preserved automatically by `RemoveLayers`'s cross-manifest check)\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go`\nThree additions:\n1. `RenameHandler` func (after `CopyHandler`, line 1350) — calls `client.Rename`, prints `\"renamed 'X' to 'Y'\"`\n2. `renameCmd` cobra command (after `copyCmd`, line 2263) — `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `cobra.ExactArgs(2)`\n3. Wire `renameCmd` into the env-docs loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand`\n\n**No new imports needed anywhere** — all required packages are already imported in each file.",
